The paper proposes a novel segmentation-based text detector that employs a Fully Convolutional Network (FCN) and a Context Attention Block to capture long-range dependencies of pixel information. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses a multi-task learning framework and integrates high-level object knowledge and low-level pixel information, indicating that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed algorithm on several benchmarks, suggesting that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
